  FIND files by date
----------------------
 1) Move all files older than 10 days from current folder to subfolder 'OLD'
   > find . -maxdepth 1 -type f -mtime +10 -exec mv {} OLD/ \;

  FIND files by size
----------------------
 1) List all files smaller than 10 bytes in current folder
   > find . -maxdepth 1 -type f -size -10c -print
   
 2) DELETE all files SMALLER than 98 bytes in current folder
   > find . -maxdepth 1 -type f -size -98c -delete
   
 3) DELETE all files LARGER than 2 Mbytes in current folder
   > find . -maxdepth 1 -type f -size +2M -delete

  Find and DELETE Files Older Than x Days
-------------------------------------------
 1) Delete files older than 90 days in <directory>
   > find <directory> -type f -mtime +90 -delete

 2) Delete, INCLUDING sub-folders, all '.log' files older than 30 days
   > find -maxdepth 9 -name "*.log" -type f -mtime +30 -delete


